SELECT 
    EXTRACT(YEAR FROM fi.DATE_KEY) AS YEAR,
    di.INDUSTRY,
    AVG(fi.AVG_STARS) AS AVG_STARS,
    SUM(fi.TOTAL_REVIEWS) AS TOTAL_REVIEWS,
    SUM(fi.TOTAL_USEFUL) AS TOTAL_USEFUL,
    SUM(fi.POSITIVE_COUNT) AS POSITIVE_COUNT,
    SUM(fi.NEGATIVE_COUNT) AS NEGATIVE_COUNT,
    SUM(fi.NEUTRAL_COUNT) AS NEUTRAL_COUNT,
    AVG(fi.AVG_SENTIMENT_SCORE) AS AVG_SENTIMENT_SCORE
FROM FACT_INDUSTRY fi
JOIN DIM_INDUSTRY di ON fi.INDUSTRY_ID = di.INDUSTRY_ID
WHERE di.INDUSTRY = 'Restaurants & Food'
GROUP BY di.INDUSTRY, YEAR
ORDER BY YEAR;

SELECT 
        dd.DAY_NAME,
        di.INDUSTRY,
        COUNT(*) AS TOTAL_REVIEWS,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY dd.DAY_NAME ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC) AS rn
    FROM FACT_REVIEWS fr
    JOIN DIM_DATE dd ON fr.DATE_KEY = dd.DATE_KEY
    JOIN DIM_INDUSTRY di ON fr.INDUSTRY_ID = di.INDUSTRY_ID
    GROUP BY dd.DAY_NAME, di.INDUSTRY
) ranked
WHERE rn = 1;

SELECT 
    dd.DAY_NAME,
    di.INDUSTRY,
    COUNT(*) AS TOTAL_REVIEWS
FROM FACT_REVIEWS fr
JOIN DIM_DATE dd ON fr.DATE_KEY = dd.DATE_KEY
JOIN DIM_INDUSTRY di ON fr.INDUSTRY_ID = di.INDUSTRY_ID
GROUP BY dd.DAY_NAME, di.INDUSTRY
QUALIFY ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY dd.DAY_NAME ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC) = 1;;

SELECT 
    di.INDUSTRY,
    SUM(db.MONDAY) AS MON,
    SUM(db.TUESDAY) AS TUE,
    SUM(db.WEDNESDAY) AS WED,
    SUM(db.THURSDAY) AS THU,
    SUM(db.FRIDAY) AS FRI,

JOIN DIM_INDUSTRY di ON fr.INDUSTRY_ID = di.INDUSTRY_ID
GROUP BY di.INDUSTRY
LIMIT 10;

JOIN DIM_INDUSTRY di ON fr.INDUSTRY_ID = di.INDUSTRY_ID
GROUP BY di.INDUSTRY;

SELECT 
    di.INDUSTRY,
    SUM(db.MONDAY) AS MON,
    SUM(db.TUESDAY) AS TUE,
    SUM(db.WEDNESDAY) AS WED,
    SUM(db.THURSDAY) AS THU,
    SUM(db.FRIDAY) AS FRI,
    SUM(db.SATURDAY) AS SAT,

JOIN DIM_INDUSTRY di ON fr.INDUSTRY_ID = di.INDUSTRY_ID
GROUP BY di.INDUSTRY;

MERGE INTO FACT_INDUSTRY AS fi
USING (
    SELECT 
        fr.INDUSTRY_ID,
        fr.DATE_KEY,
        AVG(sa.SENTIMENT_SCORE) AS AVG_SENTIMENT_SCORE,
        COUNT(CASE WHEN sa.SENTIMENT_LABEL = 'Positive' THEN 1 END) AS POSITIVE_COUNT,
        COUNT(CASE WHEN sa.SENTIMENT_LABEL = 'Negative' THEN 1 END) AS NEGATIVE_COUNT,
        COUNT(CASE WHEN sa.SENTIMENT_LABEL = 'Neutral' THEN 1 END) AS NEUTRAL_COUNT
    FROM FACT_REVIEWS AS fr
    JOIN DIM_REVIEW_SENTIMENTS AS sa 
        ON fr.REVIEW_ID = sa.REVIEW_ID
    GROUP BY fr.INDUSTRY_ID, fr.DATE_KEY
) AS src
ON fi.INDUSTRY_ID = src.INDUSTRY_ID AND fi.DATE_KEY = src.DATE_KEY
WHEN MATCHED THEN 
UPDATE SET 
    fi.AVG_SENTIMENT_SCORE = src.AVG_SENTIMENT_SCORE,
    fi.POSITIVE_COUNT = src.POSITIVE_COUNT,
    fi.NEGATIVE_COUNT = src.NEGATIVE_COUNT,
    fi.NEUTRAL_COUNT = src.NEUTRAL_COUNT;

MERGE INTO FACT_INDUSTRY AS fi
USING (
    SELECT 
        fr.INDUSTRY_ID,
        fr.DATE_KEY,
        AVG(sa.SENTIMENT_SCORE) AS AVG_SENTIMENT_SCORE,
        COUNT(CASE WHEN sa.SENTIMENT_LABEL = 'Positive' THEN 1 END) AS POSITIVE_COUNT,
        COUNT(CASE WHEN sa.SENTIMENT_LABEL = 'Negative' THEN 1 END) AS NEGATIVE_COUNT,
        COUNT(CASE WHEN sa.SENTIMENT_LABEL = 'Neutral' THEN 1 END) AS NEUTRAL_COUNT
    FROM FACT_REVIEWS AS fr
    JOIN SENTIMENT_ANALYSIS AS sa 
        ON fr.REVIEW_ID = sa.REVIEW_ID
    GROUP BY fr.INDUSTRY_ID, fr.DATE_KEY
) AS src
ON fi.INDUSTRY_ID = src.INDUSTRY_ID AND fi.DATE_KEY = src.DATE_KEY
WHEN MATCHED THEN 
UPDATE SET 
    fi.AVG_SENTIMENT_SCORE = src.AVG_SENTIMENT_SCORE,
    fi.POSITIVE_COUNT = src.POSITIVE_COUNT,
    fi.NEGATIVE_COUNT = src.NEGATIVE_COUNT,
    fi.NEUTRAL_COUNT = src.NEUTRAL_COUNT;

INSERT INTO FACT_INDUSTRY (
    industry_id, industry, date_key,
    avg_stars, total_reviews,
    total_useful, total_funny, total_cool,
    distinct_users, distinct_businesses
)
SELECT
    i.industry_id,
    i.industry,
    f.date_key,
    AVG(f.stars) AS avg_stars,
    COUNT(*) AS total_reviews,
    SUM(f.useful) AS total_useful,
    SUM(f.funny) AS total_funny,
    SUM(f.cool) AS total_cool,
    COUNT(DISTINCT f.user_id) AS distinct_users,
    COUNT(DISTINCT f.business_id) AS distinct_businesses
FROM FACT_REVIEWS f
JOIN DIM_INDUSTRY i ON f.industry_id = i.industry_id
GROUP BY i.industry_id, i.industry, f.date_key;
show WAREHOUSES like 'INDUSTRY_WH'

CREATE OR REPLACE TABLE FACT_INDUSTRY (
    industry_id INTEGER,
    industry VARCHAR(16777216),
    date_key DATE,
    avg_stars FLOAT,
    total_reviews NUMBER(38,0),
    total_useful NUMBER(38,0),
    total_funny NUMBER(38,0),
    total_cool NUMBER(38,0),
    distinct_users NUMBER(38,0),
    distinct_businesses NUMBER(38,0),
    PRIMARY KEY (industry_id, date_key)
);

INSERT INTO DIM_DATE
SELECT
    d AS DATE_KEY,
    YEAR(d) AS YEAR,
    QUARTER(d) AS QUARTER,
    MONTH(d) AS MONTH,
    TO_CHAR(d, 'Month') AS MONTH_NAME,
    WEEK(d) AS WEEK,
    DAY(d) AS DAY,
    TO_CHAR(d, 'Day') AS DAY_NAME,
    CASE WHEN DAYOFWEEK(d) IN (1, 7) THEN TRUE ELSE FALSE END AS IS_WEEKEND
FROM TABLE(GENERATOR(ROWCOUNT => 10000))  -- generates 10,000 rows
    , LATERAL (SELECT DATEADD(DAY, ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY SEQ4()) - 1, DATE '2010-01-01') AS d)
WHERE d <= DATE '2030-12-31';

CREATE OR REPLACE TABLE DIM_DATE (
    DATE_KEY DATE PRIMARY KEY,
    YEAR INT,
    QUARTER INT,
    MONTH INT,
    MONTH_NAME STRING,
    WEEK INT,
    DAY INT,
    DAY_NAME STRING,
    IS_WEEKEND BOOLEAN
);

WITH col_list AS (
  SELECT column_name
  FROM INFORMATION_SCHEMA.COLUMNS
  WHERE table_name = 'DIM_BUSINESS'
    AND table_schema = 'PUBLIC'
    AND table_catalog = 'FINAL_PROJECT'
),
null_stats AS (
  SELECT 
    column_name,
    COUNT(*) AS total_rows,
    SUM(CASE WHEN CASE column_name
      WHEN 'BUSINESS_ID' THEN IFF(BUSINESS_ID IS NULL, 1, 0)
      WHEN 'BUSINESS_NAME' THEN IFF(BUSINESS_NAME IS NULL, 1, 0)
      WHEN 'STATE' THEN IFF(STATE IS NULL, 1, 0)
      WHEN 'REVIEW_COUNT' THEN IFF(REVIEW_COUNT IS NULL, 1, 0)
      WHEN 'IS_OPEN' THEN IFF(IS_OPEN IS NULL, 1, 0)
      WHEN 'TOTAL_CHECKINS' THEN IFF(TOTAL_CHECKINS IS NULL, 1, 0)
      WHEN 'FIRST_CHECKIN' THEN IFF(FIRST_CHECKIN IS NULL, 1, 0)
      WHEN 'LAST_CHECKIN' THEN IFF(LAST_CHECKIN IS NULL, 1, 0)
      WHEN 'MONDAY' THEN IFF(MONDAY IS NULL, 1, 0)
      WHEN 'TUESDAY' THEN IFF(TUESDAY IS NULL, 1, 0)
      WHEN 'WEDNESDAY' THEN IFF(WEDNESDAY IS NULL, 1, 0)
      WHEN 'THURSDAY' THEN IFF(THURSDAY IS NULL, 1, 0)
      WHEN 'FRIDAY' THEN IFF(FRIDAY IS NULL, 1, 0)
      WHEN 'SATURDAY' THEN IFF(SATURDAY IS NULL, 1, 0)
      WHEN 'SUNDAY' THEN IFF(SUNDAY IS NULL, 1, 0)
    END = 1 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS null_count
  FROM col_list, DIM_BUSINESS
  GROUP BY column_name
)
SELECT 
  column_name,
  total_rows,
  null_count,
  ROUND(100 * null_count / total_rows, 2) AS null_percentage
FROM null_stats
ORDER BY null_percentage DESC;
